OL,3,CSouthport inquiry hears of delays in
OL,4,Cattacker's autism diagnosis
OL,6,FShe agreed she would have expected the
OL,7,Femails to trigger a prioritisation of
OL,8,Fthe teenager's case, but said at the
OL,9,Ftime there was not a process for
OL,10,Fexpediting cases.
OL,12,FShe agreed that the fact an
OL,13,Fappointment for an autism assessment
OL,14,Fwas not offered until July 2020 was a
OL,15,F"marked shortcoming".
OL,17,FAt a multi-disciplinary panel meeting
OL,18,Fon 30 December 2020 AR was diagnosed
OL,19,Fas autistic and it was recommended he
OL,20,Fwas assessed for ADHD, the inquiry
OL,21,Fheard.
